Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.83,0:00:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.84,0:00:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.84,0:00:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.85,0:00:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}are waiting for the moment\N{\c&He1e1e1&}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.53,0:00:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The words we exchange\N{\c&He1e1e1&}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.53,0:00:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and a chance meeting\N{\c&He1e1e1&}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.21,0:01:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}People, no matter who they are,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.48,0:01:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.15,0:01:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}As we leave behind a living\N{\c&He1e1e1&}testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.49,0:01:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}the Galaxy Railways on which\N{\c&He1e1e1&}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.18,0:01:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Planet Leo Glando. With the dense\N{\c&He1e1e1&}plasma layers in its atmosphere,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.85,0:01:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}this planet is famous for its\N{\c&He1e1e1&}abundant mineral resources.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.86,0:01:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Today, just like any other,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.32,0:01:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}a Galaxy Railways unmanned freight\N{\c&He1e1e1&}train heads for a plasma hole.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.87,0:01:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There has been an explosion\N{\c&He1e1e1&}within the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.47,0:02:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}on the ascension track\N{\c&He1e1e1&}on Planet Leo Glando.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.21,0:02:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sensors are detecting damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.81,0:02:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}No. 534{\i0}, which had been in motion,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}has fallen off its track,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.64,0:02:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and landed on the planet's surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.15,0:02:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Dispatch Sirius Platoon,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of the Space Defense Force!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.82,0:02:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}An encounter between two\N{\c&He1e1e1&}people is destined...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.40,0:02:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Big One Hijacked"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.52,0:02:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've detected a slight abnormality\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in {\i1}Big One{\i0}'s output relays.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.19,0:02:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}When we broke through the plasma\N{\c&He1e1e1&}layer, we probably took some damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.86,0:03:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It won't take long to repair it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay then, we'll go on ahead and see\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to about towing and salvaging {\i1}No. 534{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.80,0:03:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Once {\i1}Big One{\i0}'s repairs are complete,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}rendezvous with the advance party.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.47,0:03:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.72,0:03:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Did you want to go on ahead\N{\c&He1e1e1&}with them to the site, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.22,0:03:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sure. I only learned a little
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.43,0:03:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}about towing and salvaging\N{\c&He1e1e1&}trains in training school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.90,0:03:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Then it's no surprise why\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you were left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.57,0:03:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Rookie, stop enjoying\N{\c&He1e1e1&}your work so much!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.24,0:03:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't you go playing poker, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.58,0:03:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Come on, let's finish this up\N{\c&He1e1e1&}quickly and meet up with the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.25,0:03:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.25,0:03:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right, hook that up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.58,0:03:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.58,0:03:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}About Bruce...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.59,0:04:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Has he always been like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.52,0:04:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The SDF is not a death squadron!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.83,0:04:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you mean to commit\N{\c&He1e1e1&}suicide, go somewhere else!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.20,0:04:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, he's not that good at getting\N{\c&He1e1e1&}along with others, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.54,0:04:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Check B Panel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.87,0:04:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}R- right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.87,0:04:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I think he's a bit\N{\c&He1e1e1&}off-putting at first myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.54,0:04:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He wasn't like that before...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.55,0:04:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right, it's fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.22,0:04:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.22,0:04:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's an irregularity coming from the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}signal relays under the operations car.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.55,0:04:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey now, don't tell me all\N{\c&He1e1e1&}this has been damaged, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.23,0:04:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki, check the exterior for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.56,0:04:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.91,0:04:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}- {\i1}Big One{\i0}'s carriage signal has terminated!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}- {\i1}Big One{\i0}, come in! {\i1}Big One{\i0}, come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.58,0:04:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.25,0:05:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There is no response\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to our hails, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.52,0:05:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Declare an emergency. Order Spica Platoon\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to scramble. Have them search for {\i1}Big One{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.52,0:05:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Spica Platoon, mobilize at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.52,0:05:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Converting {\i1}Big One{\i0}'s signal data to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}trace mode. Forwarding to {\i1}No. 034{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.86,0:05:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki-{\i1}san{\i0}? Yuuki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.87,0:05:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.21,0:05:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Report, Yuuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.87,0:05:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Report? Where's {\i1}Big One{\i0}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.88,0:05:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We can't get through to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.21,0:05:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}By the time we got worried and came back,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you were already lying here, Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.22,0:05:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.89,0:05:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't know. I was investigating the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}undercarriage of the car, when suddenly-
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.56,0:05:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Didn't you see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.85,0:06:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Due to the effects of the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}composition of the soil
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.22,0:06:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and the plasma layers in the sky\N{\c&He1e1e1&}over Planet Leo Glando here,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.19,0:06:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}it is impossible to use\N{\c&He1e1e1&}any ordinary radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.52,0:06:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Currently, without any identification\N{\c&He1e1e1&}signal from the train,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.72,0:06:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}there won't be any way to search\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for {\i1}Big One{\i0} except visually.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.19,0:06:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'd like to begin the search immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.20,0:06:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Acknowledged.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.20,0:06:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So long as {\i1}Big One{\i0} has\N{\c&He1e1e1&}gotten away from us,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.37,0:06:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}we cannot allow for any\N{\c&He1e1e1&}carelessness in our communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.20,0:06:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Everyone adjust your communicator\N{\c&He1e1e1&}ranges to match Spica Platoon's.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.54,0:06:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're starting the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.54,0:06:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.88,0:06:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki, not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.55,0:06:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You've been hit over the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.88,0:06:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.21,0:06:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm fine! Let me help search for David!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.88,0:06:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's an order.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.89,0:06:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Go check yourself into Spica Platoon's\N{\c&He1e1e1&}medical car. Yuki, if you would...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.56,0:06:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.89,0:06:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Come on, Yuuki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.90,0:07:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Here I am, with one of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}my comrades missing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.19,0:07:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.53,0:07:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just start flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.20,0:07:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Good grief, you're a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}reckless one, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.20,0:07:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.87,0:07:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please be safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.50,0:08:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There she is!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.83,0:08:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is Yuuki! We've located {\i1}Big One{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.40,0:08:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}She's in sector 32, heading\N{\c&He1e1e1&}northeast on Track No. 14!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.18,0:08:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.18,0:08:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Track No. 14 dead-ends up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.52,0:08:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Look! It's a plasma hole! They're planning\N{\c&He1e1e1&}on going up through the sky there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.86,0:08:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't be ridiculous. Without an ascension\N{\c&He1e1e1&}track, not even {\i1}Big One{\i0} could do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.20,0:08:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.87,0:08:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}A transport?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.21,0:08:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That went smoother than expected, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.87,0:08:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Our reward money will be doubled for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.21,0:08:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Death Kreuz thought this\N{\c&He1e1e1&}through pretty well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.88,0:08:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Once they gets their hands\N{\c&He1e1e1&}on an SDF cosmogenerator,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.08,0:08:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}they can make as many new\N{\c&He1e1e1&}weapons as they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.22,0:09:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Which means that we space\N{\c&He1e1e1&}pirates can run wild!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.82,0:09:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Death Kreuz...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.49,0:09:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Data check on the criminal's craft is\N{\c&He1e1e1&}complete. Registration number 0282.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.50,0:09:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It matches a large transport\N{\c&He1e1e1&}carrier belonging to Death Kreuz,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.47,0:09:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}the merchants of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.83,0:09:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They're after {\i1}Big One{\i0} herself!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.17,0:09:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So they arranged this\N{\c&He1e1e1&}whole thing, did they?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.51,0:09:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.85,0:09:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Boss...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.85,0:09:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Go look through the rear cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.78,0:09:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's no need to hand this whole\N{\c&He1e1e1&}thing over to those Death Kreuz guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.52,0:09:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If there's anything that we can\N{\c&He1e1e1&}make use of, we're taking it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.19,0:09:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.53,0:09:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.87,0:09:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's Sirius Platoon's coded line.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.54,0:09:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.87,0:09:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.54,0:09:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's your situation?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Can you describe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.21,0:10:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}SDF Signals... Apparently, he's in\N{\c&He1e1e1&}a situation where he cannot speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.89,0:10:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's an emergency transmission\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from Galaxy Railways Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.89,0:10:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The Galaxy Railways Committee,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}in accordance with SDF Article 387,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.53,0:10:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}has come to a conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.90,0:10:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0} is to be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.58,0:10:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Destroy {\i1}Big One{\i0}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.25,0:10:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just a moment, please, Chief. Does\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the Supreme Commander know about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.26,0:10:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Since it is based on\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the bylaws of the SDF,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.53,0:10:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}there is no need to seek\N{\c&He1e1e1&}her judgment in the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.59,0:10:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I have a man on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.93,0:10:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do you want to allow {\i1}Big{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}One{\i0} to be misused?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.27,0:10:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you telling me to make\N{\c&He1e1e1&}her self-destruct myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.60,0:10:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If that were possible, Headquarters\N{\c&He1e1e1&}would have long since done so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.61,0:11:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right now, {\i1}Big One{\i0}'s carriage\N{\c&He1e1e1&}identification signal is off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.88,0:11:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The self-destruct code is linked to\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the carriage identification signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.22,0:11:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll leave the method up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.68,0:11:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sirius and Spica Platoons,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}carry out your duty at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.56,0:11:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Scanning complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.56,0:11:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There are five life signs.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Two are in the rear car,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.10,0:11:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}two are in the operations room,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and one is in the engine room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.57,0:11:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Judging by those signals, David\N{\c&He1e1e1&}must be in the operations room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.90,0:11:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, I'm going to hop aboard and\N{\c&He1e1e1&}stop them somehow from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.91,0:11:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Requesting your permission...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.24,0:11:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.24,0:11:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.91,0:11:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're going to derail {\i1}Big One{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.58,0:11:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Derail?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.92,0:11:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What do you mean, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.25,0:11:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That is Headquarters' decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.26,0:11:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We must destroy {\i1}Big One{\i0} before\N{\c&He1e1e1&}she reaches the transport ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.59,0:11:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}As such, that is the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}only means available.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.26,0:11:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But that's too severe!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.93,0:11:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just because Headquarters\N{\c&He1e1e1&}has decided it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.80,0:12:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}why do we have to go along with it!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.54,0:12:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.54,0:12:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm putting my faith in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.55,0:12:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're going to change the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.88,0:12:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All hands, return to base at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.90,0:12:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I won't...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.24,0:12:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, what are you doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.91,0:12:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I won't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.58,0:12:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There must be something we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.91,0:12:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's not over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.25,0:12:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.59,0:12:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Nothing is over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.59,0:13:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's show them how stubborn\N{\c&He1e1e1&}those of us who are out here are!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.20,0:13:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.54,0:13:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.54,0:13:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's a fighter closing in!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.54,0:13:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We'll be at the ship soon.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Leave it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.21,0:13:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We've got a hostage, too.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}They can't attack us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.54,0:13:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay, get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.88,0:13:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki, obey my orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.88,0:13:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please let me do this, Captain!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm going to do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.56,0:13:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Two of them were in the rear car...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.57,0:13:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, we're being left behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.24,0:13:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.57,0:13:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.58,0:13:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Now you've done it, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.52,0:14:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.53,0:14:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David, are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.19,0:14:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.53,0:14:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.53,0:14:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You can take care of me later!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}First, see to {\i1}Big One{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.53,0:14:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.21,0:14:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I- it won't stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.88,0:14:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The signal relay!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki, use the hand brake!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}In the engine room!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.22,0:14:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.18,0:15:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're almost at the end of the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.52,0:15:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Unless you'd rather die, back off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.22,0:15:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Interesting...\N{\c&He1e1e1&}You've got guts, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.90,0:15:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's go at it, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.85,0:16:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Did I have something stuck\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to my face, or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.19,0:16:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't you remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.19,0:16:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Five years ago, you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.20,0:16:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You killed my brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.20,0:16:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, I don't remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.22,0:16:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}20,000 to detonation point.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.89,0:16:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.51,0:17:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How dare you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.18,0:17:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...kill my brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.18,0:17:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.20,0:17:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How dare you kill my brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.87,0:17:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.22,0:17:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Big One{\i0}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.22,0:17:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.55,0:17:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Another 10,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.55,0:17:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We won't make it in time!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}You jump off, at least!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.89,0:17:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No way. It's not over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.49,0:18:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.51,0:18:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.52,0:18:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That brat...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.19,0:18:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Mess with me, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.53,0:18:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.20,0:18:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.55,0:18:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}500!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.83,0:19:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}400!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}200!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.50,0:19:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Stop!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.50,0:19:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.51,0:19:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.52,0:19:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please, let me go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.52,0:19:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.52,0:19:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You should celebrate more than this!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}You've pulled something incredible off!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.86,0:19:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No, I haven't...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.86,0:19:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.53,0:19:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.86,0:19:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Nicely done! What a feat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.54,0:19:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}I...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.88,0:19:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}I...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.22,0:20:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The flow of time that is destiny...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.99,0:20:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Mankind can only submit{\i0}\N{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}themselves to its flow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.90,0:20:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki Manabu, for disobeying orders,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I am announcing your punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.24,0:20:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Today is special. Just polish up the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}areas that got dirty on Leo Glando.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.92,0:20:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.92,0:20:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Maintenance men have it\N{\c&He1e1e1&}tough, huh? Drink that later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.92,0:20:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Maintenance men?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.93,0:20:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What? We have a bet!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.70,0:21:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I made a bet with the maintenance crew over\N{\c&He1e1e1&}how long it would take to clean {\i1}Big One{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.88,0:21:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.21,0:21:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you've got time to stand\N{\c&He1e1e1&}around thanking me, get to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.25,0:21:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I've got 5000 ables riding on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.22,0:21:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.22,0:21:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We'll have this done in an hour!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.55,0:21:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There's no way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.55,0:21:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Fine, wanna bet?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.22,0:21:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Sometimes, people willingly put{\i0}\N{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}their lives in other people's hands.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.23,0:21:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Together with the bonds{\i0}\N{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}that we call trust.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.18,0:21:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}How many nights have I\N{\c&He1e1e1&}spent alone since then?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.19,0:22:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Constantly having dreams of the hope\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that you are, as I lightly sleep.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.87,0:22:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The smiles and tears that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you gave to me and me alone{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.88,0:22:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}come to mind every time\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I get disheartened,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.22,0:22:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and I set forth again\N{\c&He1e1e1&}toward the morrow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.89,0:22:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}The joyful light of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the galaxy beckons me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.50,0:22:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}to that beloved person within my heart.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.51,0:22:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}No matter how far apart we are,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}my memories will never fade.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.18,0:23:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}My heart wishes always\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to be at your side.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.53,0:23:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Next Episode Preview"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.54,0:23:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}There is an outbreak of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}serial train bombings,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.17,0:23:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}and all of the SDF's\N{\c&He1e1e1&}platoons rush to the scene.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.21,0:23:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}However, seeing such a\N{\c&He1e1e1&}horrific sight, I...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.88,0:23:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Next time on Tales of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the Galaxy Railways,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.38,0:23:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}Episode 6:{\i0} "Shrieking in the Darkness"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.55,0:23:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&He1e1e1&}We're going to encounter\N{\c&He1e1e1&}something at the next station.{\i0}